The Department of Correctionl Service has condemned the discrimination and stigmatisation of its employees due to the COVID-19 pandemic. PORT ELIZABETH - Correctional Services is condemning the discrimination and stigmatisation of its employees due to the COVID-19 pandemic. The department says some employees are being turned away from shops, especially in the Eastern Cape. READ: Correctional services hits out over virus protest call Spokesperson Singabakho Nxumalo said people should educate themselves about the virus and fight the stigma surrounding it. More than 90 officials and prisoners have contracted COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.